article.headline: Kalinoski, Davidson coast past Stetson 90-59
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Tyler Kalinoski hit seven 3-pointers to match a career-high of 25 points, grabbed nine rebounds and Davidson rolled past Stetson for a 90-59 victory on Saturday. The Wildcats (6-1) sank 16 of 34 3-pointers en route to a 44.9 shooting percentage overall. Oskar Michelsen sank four from deep to finish with 16 points and Brian Sullivan had 14 with eight assists. Jack Gibbs chipped in six assists for Davidson, which finished with 25 assists on 31 field goals. Nathan Ekwu had seven points with 10 boards. Kalinoski went 8 of 12 from the field and 7 of 9 from the perimeter in tying his career-high set earlier this season in a win over Central Florida on Nov. 26. Stetson (3-7) was buried by the three ball, falling behind 48-24 at the break and trailing by 44 late. B.J. Glasford led the Hatters with 15 points and Kentwan Smith added 11.
